The SWORD Project is the CrossWire Bible Society's free Bible software
project. Its purpose is to create cross-platform open-source tools
that allow programmers and Bible societies to write new Bible software
more quickly and easily.

After installing run:
	sudo cp ${PREFIX}/share/examples/sword/sword.conf /etc/
and add to your ~/.profile:
	export SWORD_PATH=${PREFIX}/share/sword

This port for OpenBSD has been submitted upstream as a
slightly edited version of what is used in the 
Aprendiendo de Jesus OpenBSD-based distribution 
(aprendiendo.pasosdejesus.org). 
It was made originally by Vladimir Tamara Patino 
(vtamara@pasosdeJesus.org).
